    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Hymenosicyos villosus are its antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial properties. The plant's antioxidant properties, contributed by flavonoids and phenolic acids, help protect against oxidative stress and cell damage. Its anti-inflammatory properties, attributed to sesquiterpenes and triterpenoids, inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory mediators, reducing inflammation and pain. Additionally, the antimicrobial properties of Hymenosicyos villosus, mediated by saponins and volatile oils, exhibit broad-spectrum activity against bacteria, fungi, and viruses. Furthermore, the plant's antiproliferative properties, influenced by alkaloids and glycosides, have been shown to inhibit cancer cell growth and induce apoptosis.",
