    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Hymenosicyos villosus are infusion, tincture, decoction, salve, and tea. Infusion is typically prepared by steeping dried Hymenosicyos villosus leaves in hot water, which is used to treat fever and respiratory issues due to its expectorant properties. Decoction is prepared by boiling the roots of the plant, and its use is documented in traditional medicine for treating skin conditions and wounds. Tincture is prepared by soaking the plant in a solvent like ethanol or glycerin, which is used to treat various ailments including fever and rheumatism. Salve and tea preparations are also used to treat skin conditions, wounds, and fever, with salve being applied topically and tea being consumed orally.",
